                <outline text="C. Implementing Secure Systems">
                    <outline text="iv. Security Architecture (C1)  ">
                        <outline text="Design and development considerations: trusted computing base, security architecture and patterns, security models and design principles (e.g., principle of least privilege, fail-safe defaults), software (program) security, emission security "/>
                        <outline text="Selecting and applying core technologies: authentication, access control, privacy controls, security protocols "/>
                        <outline text="Recognising security needs across platforms: operating system security, Web security, embedded security, cloud and virtualisation security, security as a service "/>
                        <outline text="Cryptography: cipher and algorithm types, applications to confidentiality, integrity and authentication, PKI "/>
                        <outline text="Network security: Internet security protocols, tunnelling, VPNs, network attack and defence, TLS "/>
                        <outline text="Human factors: usable security, psychology of security, insider threat "/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="v. Secure Development (C2) ">
                        <outline text="Security systems development: managing secure systems development, principles of secure programming, formal approaches, understanding implementation errors and exploits. "/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="vi. Control Systems ">
                        <outline text="SCADA and SMART Systems, cyber system of systems (from abstract to physical effect), "/>
                        <outline text="Non-IP protocols and standards (e.g., WiFi, Bluetooth, GSM, CAN, MODBUS)"/>
                        <outline text="Cyber-physical systems analysis, embedded systems, assurance of control systems hardware and software"/>
                        <outline text="Design/implementation methodologies to minimise the risk of vulnerabilities"/>
                        <outline text="Risk modelling and risk-based decision making"/>
                    </outline>
